list.item:
At that time, picking up from Soviet pressure on this issue (illustrated, for example, by Tommy’s lunch with Dobrynin, reported in the attached message),Thompson’s discussion with Dobrynin is reported in telegram 4590 from Moscow, April 25. (National Archives and Records Administration, RG 59, Central Files 1967–69, POL 27 VIET S) we tell Moscow:
—We shall not be doing Hanoi-Haiphong bombing for a little while, but we must, of course, continue bombing north of the DMZ;
—We shall enter no commitments about the future; but they have a matter of, say, 2 or 3 weeks to deliver something by way of negotiations.
